The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Nov. 26: The proposed National Pharmaceutical Policy 2006 may finally adopt both price monitoring and control mechanism to make the 354 drugs under the national list of essential medicines cheaper. The Satwant Reddy committee, which has been asked to submit its report on the draft pharma policy, is likely to extend the November 30 deadline.

 New Delhi, Nov. 26: Berger Paints is planning to commission its $2.5-million paint manufacturing facility in Russia by January 2007, as it expects additional revenues to the tune of $3-4 million from the plant.

 New Delhi, Nov. 26: The search committee constituted for selecting the chairperson of the proposed downstream oil regulator has shortlisted the names and will meet next week to finalise the candidate for the position.

 New Delhi, Nov. 26: Punj Lloyd is keen to set up a refinery in Russia to tap that countrys vast oil reserves. The company is exploring possibilities to set up an oil refinery in the Takhtamukai region of the country.

 Tokyo, Nov. 26: Ericsson has given its nod for restructuring its Indian operations, shifting focus on multimedia in the telecom sector.




